0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12470025/comment/12897900","id":"12897900","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rhillegas","name":"rhillegas","emailAddress":"rhillegas at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Rick Hillegas","active":true},"body":"After we improve the memory usage of the LOBs returned by SQLClob.getObject() and SQLBlob.getObject() (see DERBY-4544), we should add a test case to ParameterMappingTest to test LOB inout procedure args which are bigger than the VM memory. Grep that file for makeBigClob and makeBigBlob to see where to plug in this test. This should round off the work done on DERBY-4066.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rhillegas","name":"rhillegas","emailAddress":"rhillegas at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Rick Hillegas","active":true},"created":"2010-08-12T19:15:39.245+0000","updated":"2010-08-12T19:15:39.245+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12470025/comment/13016486","id":"13016486","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rhillegas","name":"rhillegas","emailAddress":"rhillegas at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x2